enness about the new challenges involved in doing transformative work today. It develops an expansive and systematic understanding of what “transformative” can mean across the entire academic and professional context of social work education.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Social Work.2bisacsh1 aAbrams, Laura S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAharon, Tamar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarna, Jb, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBechtel, Ken, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeekman, Ratna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBobella, Alexander, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoyd, Tucker, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBuzaglo, Dedi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarruthers, Jean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClem, Kate Ball, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFook, Jan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFook, Jan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGannon, Kate, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarvey, Bc, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGupta, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeading-Grant, Wanda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIshay, Emily, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJatlow, Danielle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJatlow, Danielle, eeditor.4edt4http://i